    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Offered is a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the iconic 13B-REW rotary engine with its sophisticated sequential twin-turbocharger setup. This example maintains flawless compression across all rotor faces, with a vacuum system that remains factory-spec. The chassis retains its legendary 50/50 weight distribution, paired with a crisp 5-speed manual transmission and a limited-slip differential that provides exceptional power delivery. Every bushing is pliable, and the double-wishbone suspension geometry is perfectly dialed. This is a turn-key, investment-grade specimen with zero thermal degradation of the engine harness or interior plastics.",
